# Feature: canonical lead skill-group — the poured "bring-up-bc" SKILL.md scopes the
# BCLAUNCHER_HOST_HOME requirement to the bind-mounted-home launch case, not universally
#
# Driver: lead-jonx. The canonical bring-up-bc skill (shipped by shopsystem-templates;
# lead-held copy at .claude/skills/bring-up-bc/SKILL.md) OVERSTATES BCLAUNCHER_HOST_HOME
# as universally required for every launch ("Always set BCLAUNCHER_HOST_HOME ... the
# single most common launch-time miss"). That universal framing CONTRADICTS canonical
# bc-launcher scenario 44 (@scenario_hash:d6296d959f851be5), which pins that a clone-path
# launch does NOT require BCLAUNCHER_HOST_HOME — credentials arrive via the agent-vault
# broker, not a host bind mount. This scenario pins the corrected framing: the skill doc
# must present BCLAUNCHER_HOST_HOME as required ONLY for the workspace-mount /
# bind-mounted-home (devcontainer) launch case, and must NOT present it as required for a
# clone-path BC launch or universally for every launch.
#
# Coexistence: this is ADDITIVE to scenario 161 (@scenario_hash:cc52003444ea63f7), which
# pins that the poured SKILL.md NAMES setting BCLAUNCHER_HOST_HOME "for a devcontainer with
# a bind-mounted home". 161 survives unchanged — it asserts the requirement is NAMED for
# the bind-mounted-home case; THIS scenario asserts that same requirement is SCOPED to that
# case and not over-generalized. The two compose; neither retires the other. This scenario
# resolves the contradiction between the current overstated skill text and bc-launcher 44.
#
# Kept product/slug-neutral via the bootstrap-pour fixture, mirroring 161's style: the
# assertion is on the POURED SKILL.md content, the artifact the templates package ships.
@scenario_hash:7df4006ce0d43d8b
Scenario Outline: the poured "bring-up-bc" skill scopes the BCLAUNCHER_HOST_HOME requirement to the workspace-mount / bind-mounted-home launch case and does not present it as required for a clone-path launch or universally
  Given an existing git repository at a target directory "<target>" with no ".claude/skills/" directory
  When I invoke the "shop-templates" bootstrap entry point with shop type "<shop_type>", shop name "<shop_name>", and target directory "<target>"
  Then the exit code is 0
  And the target directory contains a file at ".claude/skills/bring-up-bc/SKILL.md"
  And the content of ".claude/skills/bring-up-bc/SKILL.md" presents setting "BCLAUNCHER_HOST_HOME" as required for the workspace-mount / bind-mounted-home devcontainer launch case
  And the content of ".claude/skills/bring-up-bc/SKILL.md" names that a clone-path BC launch does NOT require "BCLAUNCHER_HOST_HOME"
  And the content of ".claude/skills/bring-up-bc/SKILL.md" does not present "BCLAUNCHER_HOST_HOME" as universally required for every launch

  Examples:
    | shop_type | shop_name          | target                 |
    | lead      | shopsystem-product | /tmp/example-lead-shop |
